    "body": "## Goal\n\nAllow an arbiter registered for the curated Venice class to execute reliable privacy-focused inference using an operator-supplied Venice API key.\n\n## Context\n\nParent initiative: https://github.com/verdikta/verdikta-roadmap/issues/3\n\nBlocked by the shared provider and ClassID definition in `verdikta-common`. Venice offers OpenAI-compatible chat completions using bearer authentication, but the integration must preserve the class's minimum privacy classification and must not silently fall back to an unapproved Anonymized model.\n\nReferences:\n\n- https://docs.venice.ai/api-reference/api-spec\n- https://docs.venice.ai/api-reference/endpoint/chat/completions\n- https://docs.venice.ai/api-reference/endpoint/models/list\n- https://docs.venice.ai/guides/features/tee-e2ee-models\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] A Venice provider implements the existing LLM provider interface and is wired through the factory and model configuration.\n- [ ] Operators configure credentials through a documented `VENICE_API_KEY` secret; keys never reach logs, responses, or client-side bundles.\n- [ ] Requests use the supported Venice base URL and required chat-completion behavior with bounded timeouts and retries.\n- [ ] Runtime validation refuses models outside the curated class or below the required privacy classification and never silently falls back.\n- [ ] Provider, model, privacy classification, and version evidence are included in health and evaluation diagnostics without exposing secrets.\n- [ ] Installer and upgrade flows detect the class, request the required credential, validate connectivity, and preserve existing provider configuration.\n- [ ] Unit tests cover request mapping, structured responses, timeouts, rate limits, malformed responses, unavailable models, and privacy-mode mismatch.\n- [ ] A staging integration test completes a full Verdikta evaluation using the curated class.\n\n## Validation\n\nInstall or upgrade a clean staging arbiter, register it for the curated ClassID, validate its health, and complete an evaluation with an approved Venice model. Attempt an Anonymized or uncurated model and verify the request is refused before inference.\n\n## Scope\n\nIn scope:\n\n- Venice text-inference provider\n- Factory, configuration, health, installer, upgrade, tests, and operator docs\n- Operator-supplied API keys\n- Enforcement of the curated privacy boundary\n\nOut of scope:\n\n- Non-text Venice APIs\n- Automatic fallback to unapproved models\n- Storing or centrally provisioning operator API keys",
